The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Friday, June 24, 2005 

 Big B for main event 

 WILLIAM TELL

 Bangalore: V. Lokanaths ward Big B, a three-time winner in four starts, looks good for another one when he takes on eight rivals for the upper division of the 1,400m Hampi Cup on Friday. K.P. Appu partners the Pennine Ridge-Byzara four-year-old. The lower division of the trophy may see Here Comes The Sun, from the yard of Rafaat Hussain with David Badel in the saddle, tipped to win.

 SELECTIONS

 2 pm: One Touch Guy 1. Contare Su Me 2. Amanat 3.

 2.30 pm: Star Movements 1. Kilspindie 2. Super Elite 3.

 3 pm: Tinas Triumph 1. Solar Fire 2. Zando 3.

 3.30 pm: Spectacular Blaze 1. Raphaela 2. The Peak 3.

 4 pm: Big B 1. Jumping For Joy 2. Imperialism 3.

 4.30 pm: Amazing Ability 1. Turf Raider 2. Dancing Duke 3.

 5 pm: Here Comes The Sun 1. Romantic Count 2. Dr Evil 3.

 5.30 pm: Craigielaw 1. Smarty 2. Settle The Score 3.

 Days Best: Big B Double: Here Comes The Sun amp; Craigielaw




